qas.question: What german word does the term szlachta come from?
What is the polish name for knight?
Where does the word her derive from in german?

context: The term szlachta is derived from the Old High German word <a0_0>slahta<a0_0/> (modern German Geschlecht), which means <a1_0>"(noble) family"<a1_0/>, much as many other Polish words pertaining to the nobility derive from German words—e.g., the Polish "<a2_0>rycerz<a2_0/>" ("knight", cognate of the German "<a3_0>Ritter<a3_0/>") and the Polish "herb" ("coat of arms", from the German "<a4_0>Erbe<a4_0/>", "heritage").
